					<%= link_to image_tag("LogoSubscribe.png", :size => "80x70")%> is a <strong>web-mobile-based </strong>tool for <strong>creating</strong> and <strong>sharing interactive tag-based learning experiences</strong>. 
	   </div>

	   <row></row>
			<div class="span12">
				<div class="span5 well">
					<h1>etiquetAR web app</h1>
	     	 		<%= link_to image_tag("SchemaInit-CompletoPos1.png", :size => "1000x1000", alt: "etiquetAR")%>
					The EtiquetAR web application enables creating, collecting, printing and sharing personalized interactive QR. Users can associate one or more multimedia web resources to each of the QR tags. Once created, the Tags can be shared and updated by any other user of the community and grouped into collections for creating structured information paths. The QR codes can be tagged by the users to customize and glocalize objects of the urban spaces or of the cultural institutions.
	  			 </div>

	  			 <div class="span5 well">
	  			 	<h1>etiquetAR mobile app</h1>
	  			 	 <div class="span5 ">
		     	 		<%= link_to image_tag("MockupEtiquetAR-Mob_LogIn.png", :size => "80x80", alt: "etiquetAR")%>
		     	 		<%= link_to image_tag("MockupEtiquetAR-Mob_TagReader.png", :size => "80x80", alt: "etiquetAR")%>
		     	 		<%= link_to image_tag("MockupEtiquetAR-Mob_ProfileSelector.png", :size => "80x80", alt: "etiquetAR")%>
		     	 		<%= link_to image_tag("MockupEtiquetAR-Mob_ResourceVisualization.png", :size => "80x80", alt: "etiquetAR")%>
		     	 	</div>
	     	 		<br>
					The etiquetAR mobile application enables the user to interact with the tags for both, accessing to one or another resource depending of his/her interests/profile and updating its information. In this context, QR codes behave as “citizen sensors” that benefit from citizens' interactions to capture their intentions, worries and interests about the urban context.
	  			 </div>

